The paper discusses the use of mobile edge computing (MEC) to improve the performance of wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of queueing theory and stochastic geometry to analyze the performance of the network, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the effects of network parameters and bias factors on the performance of the network, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of MEC for computation resulting data, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
